    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix signal_energy_nodc function variable typo\n\n### Summary\nThere is a typo in the variable name within the `signal_energy_nodc` function that causes incorrect calculation of leftover samples. The variable `lefover_count` should be `leftover_count`.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/signal_energy.c`: Fixed typo in variable name from `lefover_count` to `leftover_count` on line 81 and updated its usage on line 82.\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running UE signal measurements with specific frame configurations, the energy calculation may return incorrect values due to the undefined behavior of the typoed variable. This can lead to inaccurate RSRP/RSRQ measurements and potentially affect cell selection and handover decisions.\n\nTo reproduce:\n1. Configure UE with specific RB allocation that results in leftover samples\n2. Run LTE measurements procedure\n3. Observe incorrect power measurements in the UE logs\n\n"
}